Classes in com.poesys.db.pk used by com.poesys.db.pk
AbstractMultiValuedPrimaryKey
          Implements the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from multiple values.
AbstractPrimaryKey
          An abstract implementation of the IPrimaryKey interface that is the parent of all the other primary key implementations, sharing code that all or most classes use.
AbstractSingleValuedPrimaryKey
          Implements the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from a single value.
AssociationKeyMapping
           A helper class that represents the mapping of names in a list of foreign keys in an association.
AssociationPrimaryKey
          A concrete implementation of the IPrimaryKey interface that represents an association primary key.
CompositePrimaryKey
          A concrete implementation of the IPrimaryKey interface that represents a composite primary key.
GuidPrimaryKey
          Implements the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from a single GUID value as a string.
IdentityPrimaryKey
          Implements the abstract single-valued primary key and the IPrimaryKey interface for a key constructed from a single integer value created by an identity or auto-increment column (a column that gets its value generated automatically when you insert and which you do not supply through the INSERT statement).
IPrimaryKey
          A generic interface for primary key classes that represent a set of columns and values that uniquely identify an object.
NaturalPrimaryKey
           Implements the IPrimaryKey interface with a multi-valued column primary key comprising any number of arbitrary columns.
SequencePrimaryKey
           Implements the single-valued primary key for a key constructed from a single integer value created dynamically from a SEQUENCE or some other, similar mechanism.
